		<outline title="<![CDATA[Crusade]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/crusade/feed" type="rss" htmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/crusade/" text="<![CDATA[Crusade]]>" description="<![CDATA[A drug-fueled crusade by two deranged journalists assigned to look into the morass of organized religion. Cornholery, snake handlers, faith healers, serial killers, sarcasm, blasphemy-good, clean, American fun.]]>"/>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Dunkin the Vampire Slayer]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/dunkin-the-vampire-slayer/feed" type="rss" htmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/dunkin-the-vampire-slayer/" text="<![CDATA[Dunkin the Vampire Slayer]]>" description="<![CDATA[What could possibly bring together a 450 pound vampire slayer, a drunken, acid-tongued detective, a good natured carpenter, bureaucratic vampires, giant anacondas, mutant vampire bats, Ho Hos, Twinkies and more one-liners than a night at the comedy club? Dunkin, the vampire slayer blends all this discordance and more into a hilarious adventure that moves from the muggy heat of Florida to the muggier heat of the Amazon. ....If Carl Hiaasson, Tim Dorsey and Dave Barry collaborated on a vampire story, it may have turned out like this absurd romp....]]>"/>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Dunkin the Vampire Slayer II: Death Rides A Pale, Pink, Porcine Horse]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/dunkin-the-vampire-slayer-two/feed" type="rss" htmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/dunkin-the-vampire-slayer-two/" text="<![CDATA[Dunkin the Vampire Slayer II: Death Rides A Pale, Pink, Porcine Horse]]>" description="<![CDATA[From the Smoky mountains of America, to Nepal, France, Australia, Italy, these three are on a quest that spans the globe. A quest to rid the earth of the bloodsuckers and find a cure for that nasty vampire blood. Many things stand in their way, high council vampires, hit men, ninjas, ancient  prophecies, and an unspeakable horror unleashed on the world by desperate vampires. And worst of all, Devlin&#039;s having serious anger issues as he comes to grips with being more powerful and more of a jackass than anything on earth.... oh, and more jokes, one-liners, and wiseass comments than should be allowed in any single novel.]]>"/>
